type="other" type="publication">W.Chr. 62</bibl><bibl subtype="other" type="publication">CPGr II 20</bibl><bibl subtype="other" type="publication">C.Pap.Jud. II 427</bibl></listBibl></div><div n="meta.9450" part="N" subtype="translations" type="bibliography"><head>Übersetzungen</head><listBibl lang="de"><head lang="de">Deutsch:</head><bibl type="translations">TUAT, N.F. 1 (2004), VII 43.</bibl></listBibl><listBibl lang="en"><head lang="de">Englisch:</head><bibl type="translations">Johnson, Roman Egypt (1936), S. 249, Nr. 141</bibl></listBibl></div><div n="meta.9450" part="N" subtype="locations" type="history"><p><placeName cert="high" type="ancientFindspot">Apollonias</placeName> (<geogName cert="high" type="nome">Arsinoites</geogName>), <geogName cert="high" key="Aegyptus" type="ancientRegion">Egypt</geogName></p></div><div n="meta.9450" part="N" type="figure"><p><figure href="http://ipap.csad.ox.ac.uk/4DLink4/4DACTION/IPAPwebquery?vPub=BGU&amp;vVol=4&amp;vNum=1068"><figDesc>Abbildung im Internet</figDesc></figure></p></div><div lang="de" n="tran.9450" part="N" type="translation"><p>
            <milestone n="1" unit="line"/>An Isidô[ros, den 
            <term target="basilikosgrammateus">Königlichen] Schreiber</term> des 
            Hêrakleidês-Bezirks des Arsinoïtês,
            <milestone n="3" rend="break" unit="line"/>von Sôtelês, Sohn des Iôsêpos, des Sohnes des Theomnas, 
            und der Mutter Erôtion, aus dem Dorf [A]pollônias.
            <milestone n="6" rend="break" unit="line"/>Mein Sohn I[ôs]êpos, Sohn der Sarra, minderjährig, noch nicht 
            ausgeschieden (aus der Gruppe der Minderjährigen und überführt) zur 
            <term target="laographia">Kopfsteuer</term>, ist 
            gestorben im Monat Tybi des gegenwärtigen vierten Jahres des Traianus Caesar, des 
            Herren. <milestone n="11" unit="line"/>Hiermit bitte ich darum, daß er 
            <term target="taxistonteteleutekoton">unter die Verstorbenen</term> 
            aufgenommen wird.
            <milestone n="13" rend="break" unit="line"/>(2. Hand) An den 
            <term target="komogrammateus">Dorfschreiber</term>. Wenn er gestorben ist, dann 
            <app type="BGU"><lem>registriere</lem><wit><bibl>BL VIII, S. 40</bibl></wit></app> (ihn) und 
            <app type="BGU"><lem>gib</lem><wit><bibl>BL IX, S. 25</bibl></wit></app> (darüber) eine eidliche handschriftliche 
            Erklärung ab, wie üblich.
            <milestone n="14" rend="break" unit="line"/>Im 4. Jahr des Imperator Caesar Nerva Traian[us] Augustus Germanicus 
            am <app type="BGU+DDbDP"><lem>16.</lem><wit><bibl>BGU IV 1068; Chrest. Wilck. 62; CPJ II 427</bibl></wit></app> 
            Mecheir.
            <milestone n="18" rend="break" unit="line"/>(3. Hand) Ich, der oben genannte Sôtelês, 
            Sohn des Iôsêpos, schwöre beim Imperator Caesa[r <app type="BGU+DDbDP"><lem>Nerva] Traian[us Optimus] 
                Augustus [Germanicus]</lem><wit><bibl>PACKMANN, ZPE 89, 1991, S. 101 f.</bibl></wit></app> 
            <gap extent="unknown" reason="illegible" unit="character"/>
        </p></div><div lang="en" n="tran.9450" part="N" type="translation"><p>
            <milestone n="1" unit="line"/>To Isido[ros], <term target="basilikosgrammateus">royal scribe</term> 
            of the Arsinoite nome, Themistos division,
            <milestone n="3" rend="break" unit="line"/>from Soteles, son of Josepos, the son of Theomnas, mother Erotion, 
            from the village of Apollonias.
            <milestone n="6" rend="break" unit="line"/>My son J[os]epos, mother Sarra, a minor, who had not yet ceased (to 
            be a minor) with respect to the <term target="laographia">poll-tax</term>, died in the month of Tybi of the present 
            fourth year of Traianus Caesar, the lord. <milestone n="11" unit="line"/>Therefore I request that he is 
            included amongst <term target="taxistonteteleutekoton">those, who have died</term>.
            <milestone n="13" rend="break" unit="line"/>(m. 2) To the 
            <term target="komogrammateus">village scribe</term>. If he died, 
            <app type="BGU"><lem>register</lem><wit><bibl>BL VIII 40</bibl></wit></app> him and <app type="BGU"><lem>make a report with a 
                written sworn statement</lem><wit><bibl>BL IX 25</bibl></wit></app>, as usual.
            <milestone n="15" rend="break" unit="line"/>Year 4 of Imperator Caesar Nerva Traianus Augustus Germanicus, 
            Mecheir <app type="BGU+DDbDP"><lem>16</lem><wit><bibl>BGU IV 1068; Chrest. Wilck. 62; CPJ II 427</bibl></wit></app>.
            <milestone n="18" rend="break" unit="line"/>(m. 3) I, Soteles, son of Josepos, the above 
            mentioned, swear by Imperator Caesa[r <app type="BGU+DDbDP"><lem>Nerva] Traian[us Optimus] Augustus 
                [Germanicus]</lem><wit><bibl>Packmann, ZPE 89, 1991, 101-102</bibl></wit></app> <gap extent="unknown" reason="illegible" unit="character"/>
        </p></div></body></text></TEI.2>